cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CC, cs.AI, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a soundness and completeness proof for propositional intuitionistic calculus, which is a logical system. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the semantics of computability logic, which can be seen as a programming language for interactive computational problems. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper deals with the strength of computational problems and their combinations. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper discusses the interpretation of formulas as interactive computational problems, which is a topic relevant to AI. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible category as the paper deals with the semantics of a computational logic, which can be seen as a foundation for machine learning algorithms.
